<br>
The Latest Patch Message:<br>
<br>
&quot;We would also like to bring your attention to afew more class balancing issues.<br>
<br>
Warriors now have the innate ability of Permanent Gnome Illusion. This is not an Alternate Ability, so training in this is not necessary or optional. These illusions will have only 1 arm, so expect Melee damage output to be decreased.<br>
<br>
Anyone wearing purple will now be Death Touched by Fear Golems every 15 seconds. It does not matter if they are in the Plane of Fear or not. In addition, we have once more changed the Ragefire encounter. Now, in order to get Ragefire to spawn clerics must gather 100 Pearlescent Fragments and turn them in all at once. We realize that the most you can have in inventory at once is 80 items.<br>
<br>
Shaman now have the capability to Resurrect. It should be noted that there are a number of steps involved in this procedure. The Shaman will meet the recently deceased character at a portal closest to the characters corpse. The Shaman will cast Spirit of the Wolf and Invisibility on that character. The Shaman will then escort them back to their corpse. When the corpse is reached, the Shaman will point to the corpse and say, “Loot up!”. Experience reimbursement will be minimal, if any.<br>
<br>
To counteract Rangers who have gained Archery Mastery 3 and Endless Quiver, Rangers will now have a permanent Snare effect on their character.<br>
<br>
All Bard armor is now pink. All/All armor pieces will retain their original color schemes on any other character type, other than Bards. Upon reaching the 60th level, Bards will receive the Lisp ability.<br>
<br>
Enchanters will find a new spell available to them at level 1. “Flowing Platinum” can be found at any vendor location throughout Everquest. Casting this will give the Enchanter 10,000 pieces of platinum. Recast time is 1 second.<br>
<br>
To promote the creation of more Beastlords, all new Beastlord characters will now have GM status and be able to summon any item in game.<br>
<br>
Druids and Wizards will now be available to port to Surefall Glade. Only Surefall Glade. All other portals have been removed. We realize this will make it a long run for the Shaman who is Resurrecting someone.<br>
<br>
Nexus Scions have had their faction adjusted so that all Player Characters are now KOS. We do not anticipate there ever being a way to raise this faction.<br>
<br>
After receiving numerous complaints from our Wizard community regarding the recent changes to Manaburn, we have modified this a bit. To counteract Manaburn only being able to be cast on an NPC once every minute, the refresh rate to re-use Manaburn has been moved down to 30 seconds. The wizard, however, will only be able to target themselves for the next 3 game days.<br>
<br>
Mage pets must now be kept on a leash. Leashes are required for summoning any and all mage pets. Leashes can be purchased from vendors for more money than you have. We have instituted the calculation of (YourPP * 1.5) to determine how much leashes will be sold for.<br>
<br>
Shadow Knights will now have the permanent effect of Gather Shadows. They will not be able to attack when in this mode.<br>
<br>
Rogues will now only be able to use Sneak and Hide when they are the only PC or NPC in a zone. In addition, Lockpicking can now only be used in zones in which there are no doors.<br>
<br>
We realize that reducing Monks AC was not balanced. We are now reducing all Monk stats equally.<br>
